article.headline: Illinois St. 60, S. Illinois 57
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Champ Oguchi scored 15 points, including seven in extra time, to lead Illinois State to a 60-57 overtime win over Southern Illinois on Wednesday night. Lloyd Phillips had 11 points and Emmanuel Holloway and Osiris Eldridge each added 10 points for Illinois State (19-4, 8-4 Missouri Valley), which came back from a 25-17 halftime deficit. Phillips scored the last five points of regulation, including a layup and three free throws, to tie the game at 49. The Salukis' Justin Bocot missed a 3-pointer with three seconds left in overtime. Southern Illinois (10-13, 5-7) played without star Bryan Mullins, who is out indefinitely with a stress fracture in his right foot. Kevin Dillard led Southern Illinois with 20 points. Carlton Fay added 10 points. Illinois State beat Southern Illinois 70-63 when the teams last met on Jan. 24.
